ght=3D"166"></span></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"f21cbc0b6255"><strong><span data-colorid=3D"euxy01l86z">2. D=
eveloper Login (SSO Bypass)</span></strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"97f84ee634ff">During development/testing, a developer bypass=
 mode is available so that Azure AD SSO is not required. This bypass will b=
e removed in production when full Azure AD authentication is enabled.</p>
<p local-id=3D"6aff23303cc9"><strong>Step 1: </strong>Open the deployed URL=
 in your browser.</p>
<p local-id=3D"63cc25e96551"><strong>Step 2: </strong>On the login page, lo=
ok for the "Developer Login" option.</p>
<p local-id=3D"b1fb8c0ddc74"><strong>Step 3: </strong>Click "Developer Logi=
n" or enter the dev bypass token if prompted.</p>
<p local-id=3D"dab06b889f5e"><strong>Step 4: </strong>You should be redirec=
ted to the home/dashboard page.</p>
<p local-id=3D"75935224c84b"><strong><span class=3D"legacy-color-text-green=
2">Expected Result: </span></strong>You are logged in and can see the proje=
ct dashboard. The navigation bar shows your user identity or a dev indicato=
r.</p>
<p local-id=3D"ed34d857ea7e"><strong><span data-colorid=3D"kxw8y7qkru">Note=
: </span></strong>If Azure AD SSO is configured and working, you can also t=
est with "Sign in with Microsoft" which will go through the full SSO flow.<=
/p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-left-wrapper confl=
uence-embedded-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image image-l=
eft" width=3D"468" loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"7610e2e269c11b568495ea3c6ea13948=
