 data-media-id=3D"6d47cf49-e5e9-4ff9-89d5-77096de7059d" data-media-type=3D"=
file" height=3D"213"></span>
<p local-id=3D"a2a371fa3389"></p>
<p local-id=3D"bf10328e66bb"><strong><span data-colorid=3D"w7bmxo0wcy">3. P=
roject Creation / Selection</span></strong></p>
<p local-id=3D"41c2bf617e92">Each project links to a Jira project and a Con=
fluence space, enabling bi-directional sync and BRD management.</p>
<p local-id=3D"1b1f3ce8e56b"><strong>Step 1: </strong>Click "Create New Pro=
ject" on the dashboard (or select an existing project).</p>
<p local-id=3D"1777ae8f31b9"><strong>Step 2: </strong>Fill in the project d=
etails:</p>
<p local-id=3D"42e3f7d21055" style=3D"margin-left: 30.0px;">=E2=80=A2 Proje=
ct Name =E2=80=94 a descriptive name for the project<br>
=E2=80=A2 Jira Project =E2=80=94 select the linked Jira project from the dr=
opdown<br>
=E2=80=A2 Confluence Space =E2=80=94 select the linked Confluence space fro=
m the dropdown</p>
<p local-id=3D"24a4705f6b9f"><strong>Step 3: </strong>Click "Create Project=
".</p>
<p local-id=3D"94f113ff14e5"><strong>Step 4: </strong>Verify the project ap=
pears on the dashboard with the correct Jira and Confluence links.</p>
<p local-id=3D"f0e05cb88239"><strong><span class=3D"legacy-color-text-green=
2">Expected Result: </span></strong>Project is created and visible on the d=
ashboard. The Jira project key and Confluence space key are displayed.</p>
<p local-id=3D"9ebd597e98cf"><strong><span data-colorid=3D"aca1aihfg4">Note=
: </span></strong>If Jira/Confluence dropdowns are empty, verify that the b=
ackend has valid Atlassian credentials configured and that the sync service=
 is running.</p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-left-=
wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-=
